The significance of ECG examination lies in: it is used to examine various arrhythmias, ventricular atrial hypertrophy, myocardial infarction, myocardial ischemia and other diseases.

ECG is the process of electrical activity that reflects the heart\'s excitement. It has important reference value for the basic function of the heart and its pathological research. ECG can analyze and identify a variety of arrhythmias; it can also reflect the extent and development of myocardial damage and the functional structure of the atria and ventricles. It has reference value in guiding the operation of heart surgery and indicating the necessary drug treatment.

SpO2 refers to the percentage of HbO2 which can be combined with oxygen in the total capacity and that is to say, the oxygen concentration in the blood, which is an important physiological parameter of the respiratory cycle.

The SpO2 of a normal human body should be 98%. It is generally believed that SpO2 should be at least 94%. If it is less than that, hypoxia can be confirmed. It is regarded as hypoxia when the arterial blood oxygen concentration is PaO2<80mmHg on clinic, which is basically equivalent to severe hypoxemia.

1. Wrist temperature means the temperature measured by the wrist. The wrist temperature is usually lower than the normal body temperature; body temperature means the temperature of the human body.
2. The temperature of the human body is maintained at about 37 ℃ (98.6 ℃), which is quite normal.

3. Human body temperature will vary with time. Human body temperature is lower in the early morning and slightly higher in the evening. Therefore, there is a slight difference in body temperature measurement results within a day, which is normal.\n The body temperature after exercise and eating is slightly higher than when it is quiet. Muscle activity can significantly increase heat production, resulting in a rise in body temperature. Mental stress and emotional agitation can also increase body temperature, and in some cases, the body temperature can rise to 2℃ (35.6℉).
